92
00:04:04,989 --> 00:04:08,409
“All peoples of China fully enjoy freedom
of religion

93
00:04:08,409 --> 00:04:10,540
in accordance with the law."

94
00:04:10,540 --> 00:04:12,480
Speaking of saying one thing and doing another,

95
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:15,809
the Chinese regime has approached the World
Trade Organization

96
00:04:15,809 --> 00:04:18,280
for permission to sanction the US.

97
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:20,870
You know, the same World Trade Organization
whose rules

98
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:24,000
China has violated dozens of times.

99
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:28,620
China’s push for sanctions is based on a
2013 complaint it made

100
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:32,630
about the anti-dumping duties the US had put
on China.

101
00:04:32,630 --> 00:04:35,420
They were designed to offset the artificially
low cost

102
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:39,860
of Chinese imports that were undercutting
US manufacturing.

103
00:04:39,860 --> 00:04:42,510
But how the US calculated those dumping duties

104
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:45,780
was found to have been illegal in a string
of trade disputes

105
00:04:45,780 --> 00:04:47,210
brought to the WTO.

106
00:04:47,210 --> 00:04:50,160
But don’t worry, those sanctions on the
US

107
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:52,390
